The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 October is 4,458 (516 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 October, there were 378 new confirmed cases (43.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 365 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 4% ( 13 extra cases).
